article.description: — Ben Wright scored layups a minute apart and William & Mary posted a 58-57 come-from-behind win over Richmond Saturday night.
article.headline: Dorsey has 15, William & Mary defeats Richmond 58-57
article.linkText: Dorsey has 15, William & Mary defeats Richmond 58-57
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. -- — Ben Wright scored layups a minute apart and William & Mary posted a 58-57 come-from-behind win over Richmond Saturday night. Gabe Dorsey scored 15 points, shooting 5 for 13, including 5 for 12 from beyond the arc for the Tribe (4-5). Ben Wight scored 14 points while shooting 7 of 12 from the field, and added five rebounds. Anders Nelson recorded 13 points and was 5 of 11 shooting (3 for 6 from distance). The Spiders (3-5) were led by Tyler Burton, who recorded 26 points and three steals. Richmond also got 10 points and two blocks from Neal Quinn. In addition, Isaiah Bigelow had five points and six rebounds. Dorsey scored 12 points in the first half for William & Mary, who led 38-21 at halftime. Wight led William & Mary with six points in the second half as his team was outscored by 16 points over the final half but held on for the victory. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
